```

### Tailwind Best Practices
- Use semantic class ordering:
  1. Layout (flex, grid)
  2. Spacing (padding, margin)
  3. Sizing (width, height)
  4. Typography
  5. Colors
  6. Other styles

```tsx
// ✅ Well-organized Tailwind classes
<div className="
  flex items-center justify-between  // Layout
  p-4 my-2                          // Spacing
  w-full h-16                       // Sizing
  text-lg font-medium              // Typography
  bg-slate-100 text-slate-900     // Colors
  rounded-lg shadow-sm            // Other
">
```

## Performance Optimization

### Server Components
- Default to React Server Components
- Only use 'use client' when necessary:
```typescript
// ✅ Client Component when needed
'use client';

import { useState } from 'react';

export function InteractiveComponent() {
  const [state, setState] = useState(false);
  // ...
}
```

### Dynamic Loading
```typescript
// ✅ Dynamic imports for optimal loading
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic';

const HeavyComponent = dynamic(() => import('./HeavyComponent'), {
  loading: () => <LoadingSpinner />,
  ssr: false
});
```

### Image Optimization
```typescript
// ✅ Optimized image usage
import Image from 'next/image';

export function OptimizedImage() {
  return (
    <Image
      src="/image.webp"
      alt="Description"
      width={800}
      height={600}
      loading="lazy"
      className="object-cover"
    />
  );
}
```

## Anti-patterns to Avoid

❌ Don't:
- Use class components
- Implement unnecessary state management
- Write redundant code
- Use inline styles
- Create deeply nested components
- Use `any` type
- Leave console.logs in production code

✅ Do:
- Write pure functions
- Use TypeScript strictly
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Follow the single responsibility principle
- Use proper type annotations
- Implement proper loading states 
